A Gauteng Health Department Official collects samples from a man during a door-to-door COVID-19 coronavirus testing drive in Yeoville, Johannesburg. JOHANNESBURG - The COVID-19 death toll in South Africa has increased to 11. The latest fatalities are an 82-year-old woman admitted to ICU last week and an 86-year-old man who had underlying conditions. The number of confirmed cases is at 1655. READ: Rea Vaya bus impounded for overloading Minister of Health Dr Zwelini Mkhize confirmed the new statistics for the country in a statement released on Sunday night. Health Media Release 05.04.20 Final.pdf by eNCA.com on Scribd  The number of confirmed infections in Gauteng is at 704, the highest in the country. Confirmed cases in the Western Cape is at 454, followed by KwaZulu-Natal with 246. READ: Bridal couple and guests arrested on wedding day The total number of tests conducted to date is at 56 873. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.